values:
Leigh and I lit Bradferd's popcorn on fire during lunch. It kept smoking for a while (after the flame died down) and Brad smells like burnt popcorn now. I don't know why he decided to stuff it in his lunchbox. It was pretty... exciting.

 I've decided that if we ever have an actual fire we are going to die, because the fire alarm didn't go off at all. Heehee...

 Weekend! So relieved. *-* I'm gonna listen to some good music, get lost inside my head, and pratice projection! 

 *flops to the floor*
 Oww.
 I'll clean my rooom first.

*leans into your ear and whispers* My math teacher knows where my blog is. Hullo Mrs. Evans! I haven't done your homework yet! Heehee... XD

 Worried about the report card... Kind of. EVERYONE did terrible this marking period. @___@
 I think this marking period school is a little more interesting. I don't know why.

 I'm chilling out and drawing air shots of my made-up civilizations. I'm a geek! Yay for geek! :B

New seats and moderately more interesting units are this marking period... get my report card on Tuesday...
 Math-75 *wheeze wheeze*
 Science-85 
 English-over 95
 Art-98(you can't fail Art unless you try)
 Global-over 95
 
 Spanish- To be annouced, not looking nice though...

 Alas, alas, bad times, bad times. 

 Good news, this marking period looks tre interesting! I may actually learn something. :P

Only 18 more days till I go to California to leave all ya'all suckers in New York (and Massachusettes ^_~).  Muahahah. 

 I'd like to write that I'm being ultra-productive and using my young life and reaching for the stars, etc etc, but I'm not. :P I should really go do something interesting. I think... I shall meditate. :O
Fromage means cheese!! <3<3 Thanks to Taylor for my name. XD
